###### dir () function in python is used to get the list of all the attributes and methods of an object. It returns a list of strings that represent the names of the attributes and methods of the object. The output will include both built-in attributes and methods as well as any user-defined attributes and methods associated with the object. This function is useful for exploring the capabilities of an object and understanding its behavior in Python.
